reviews.review: Good movie and of course a feel good ending. It’s a bit slow in the beginning until the story gets going. Fitting end to the saga.

This movie was so bad it felt like the rushed game of thrones ending. I have lost faith in Disney's ability to make full length movies and Star Wars in general. Disney really should have just adapted the insane amount of books, comics, & video game stories instead of making all of that not canon. This movie is proof Disney has lost touch entirely. This was such a disappointment I will not support any Disney movies in theaters going forward. I will wait for a bootleg.

After the disaster known as the last Jedi, I went into this movie ready to hate it and I was ready to disown Star Wars forever, but as soon as the movie ended I realized I really enjoyed this movie! It’s not perfect but it’s an awesome conclusion to the story the force awakens started and also to the other 6 movies. This movie has a lot going on but personally I do not blame that on JJ Abrams, I blame it on Rian Johnson. This movie bummed me out, because it made me realize how this could have been an amazing trilogy if JJ had control of all 3 movies. Like I said, this movie isn’t perfect, but it’s still really good!

I've been a Star Wars Fan since the first episode came out and have all of the Star Wars Movies on Blu-Ray.  I'll buy this one as well.  I especially liked how the characters were tied together at the end.  While there was nothing I disliked, my Wife did think that the ending could have tied the main characters together more romantically.

As he did with The Force Awakens,  Abrams heavily borrows from previous Star Wars "Legend" but does so in an effective way that benefits canon and makes for captivating viewing. 

Things do seem a little rushed at times, but considering Abrams had to try to fit the story line of two movies into one, it is understandable. 

JJ Abrams did a fantastic job of making up for the disaster that was The Last Jedi and closes out the Skywalker Saga on a high note!

Ignore the critics complaining of fan service and the YouTube and Reddit Trolls! Go see Rise of Skywalker!
